{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/8116", "repo": "rails", "body": "@rafaelfranca I think in an ideal world we'd have the `:counter_cache` option on the `has_many` and have the `belongs_to` use `:inverse_of` to infer the name of the column.\r\n\r\nFor that reason I wouldn't be against us adding a `:counter_cache` option to `has_many`, but I also think that your idea of inferring from `:inverse_of` where possible is a good one. They are not mutually exclusive.", "_id": {"$oid": "5237f5d8bd3543c15100ace0"}, "issue_id": 8116, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/10207246", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/8116#issuecomment-10207246", "updated_at": "2012-11-08T22:10:51Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton", "login": "jonleighton", "gravatar_id": "2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98", "html_url": "https://github.com/jonleighton", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F798cebccb32617ad94123450fd137104.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 1979, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2012-11-08T22:10:51Z", "id": 10207246, "owner": "rails"}
